Brazil Inflation May Top Target Range This Year, Hamilton Says

-- B y   A r n a l d o   G a l v a o
-- 
2011-09-29T14:33:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/brazil-inflation-may-top-target-range-this-year-hamilton-says.html
Brazil ’s inflation could be above
the top of policy makers’ target range this year, Carlos
Hamilton, central bank economic policy chief, said.  The central bank’s projection is for 6.4 percent inflation
this year, Hamilton said to reporters in Brasilia. The number
could come in above or below that, he said.  Brazil targets inflation of 4.5 percent plus or minus two
percentage points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Arnaldo Galvao in Brasilia Newsroom at 
 agalvao1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Harry Maurer at 
